cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.HC. 

The paper deals with building a fashion recommendation system that uses visual information to retrieve visually similar and fashionable items. This involves learning a low-dimensional visual space and fashion trends from large corpora of binary feedback data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), which deals with image and video processing, analysis, and understanding. 

The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to recommend visually similar items, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. 

The use of large corpora of data and machine learning techniques to learn fashion trends and recommend fashionable items makes cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper also involves designing a graphical interface for users to explore visually similar and fashionable items, which makes cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category.
